																 PFSWeb - Supply Chain Management
															







													About the Product
												

													PFSweb solutions are based on direct experience in your marketplace. They support manufacturers with supply chain initiatives that cover the globe as well as the channel spectrum, including B2B, dealer channels, mass merchants, and B2C models.
													







														Product Description
													

														As the lifeline between your company and your customers, your supply chain should enhance your profitability as well as your supplier and customer relationships. Your business depends on it.

At PFSweb, your supply chain is their business. They can tailor a comprehensive supply chain management program that provides your company with flexible and best-in-class services, improves available to promise, expands transportation visibility, reduces overall transportation cost, and enables supply chain optimization.

Combining their proprietary software, supporting services, hardware, and appropriate third-party products, PFSweb's team of experts will tailor your custom-fit supply chain solution. Their proactive supply chain management services can include:

Materials Planning
Procurement
Extended Supply Chain Visibility
Supplier Relationship Management
Time-Definite Delivery
Document Creation and Management
Customs Brokerage
Systems Collaboration
Daily Program Coordination and Management

PFSweb provides the supply chain tools and implement the strategies and processes that deliver for many industry-leading companies whose supply chains are time-sensitive, cost-susceptible, and critical to survival.

Key Features

Data-Rich Shipment Detail
Visibility to Product Inventory (from the contract manufacturer, in transit to warehouse, and in the warehouse)
SKU Management through Kitting and Assembly
Real-Time Supplier Delivery Coordination
Event Notification and Alerts
Rules-Based Load Optimization, Carrier Selection, and Tendering

Key Benefits

Reduced Inventory Carry Costs
Improved Delivery Coordination
Improved Product Delivery Scheduling
Product Available at Promised Date
Supply Chain Compression and Optimization
Enhanced Customer Experience






														Inquire Now
													





